{
  "texts": [
    "Property rights and usage restrictions on donated biomaterials used to generate organoids also require clarification (Boers et al., 2019a,b).",
    "Data protection and privacy are additional legal considerations, given the personal nature of organoids derived from individuals' cells.",
    "Formulating adapted guidelines can outline ethical requirements, boundaries, and best practices tailored to cerebral organoid research across various translational phases (Kimmelman et al., 2016; Munsie et al., 2017).",
    "This can provide researchers a decision-making framework regarding permissible applications.",
    "Such guidelines will likely require iterative refinement as both the science and ethics evolve."
  ]
}